            Restart Research Procedures
          Heading link



 
Copy link



EHSO has established requirements that must be completed to ensure the health and safety of the research community on campus. All 3 steps below must be completed before resuming research or starting new research projects.





                            1. Register Lab with BioRAFT
                    








            1. Register Lab with BioRAFT
          

All Principal Investigators (PIs) must register with BioRAFT, a research management tool that tracks all labs, lab members, research hazards, and safety training requirements.

Sign in at https://uic.bioraft.com using your UIC NetID and password
Follow the instructions at Safe Return to Research with BioRaft to:

Identify your building, labs and work spaces, and contact information
Indicate your group’s emergency operational status
Add all research group members and identify research activities






      Instructions: Safe Return to Research with BioRaft
    



      PI Quick Start Guide for Registering a Laboratory
    



      BioRAFT FAQ
    









                            2. Complete the COVID-19 Lab Reopening Checklist
                    








            2. Complete the COVID-19 Lab Reopening Checklist
          


Sign in at https://uic.bioraft.com using your UIC NetID and password
Follow the instructions at Safe Return to Research with BioRaft or the steps below:

Go to Self Inspections in left pane and hit Add a new Self Inspection on right side
Choose COVID-19 Lab Reopening Checklist from drop-down
Hit Inspect button at the bottom, COVID-19 Pandemic Findings will populate
Add details under each check point and hit Save button
EHSO will review in few days



Frequently Asked Questions

Can one of my students help me complete the checklist? Yes. Select checkbox next to Group Compliance Liaison / CHO of desired lab member.




      Instructions: Safe Return to Research with BioRaft
    



      Printable version of the Lab Reopening Checklist
    



      BioRAFT FAQ
    









                            3. Receive College and Department Approval
                    








            3. Obtain College and Department Approval
          

Dean and department head will provide final approval for research operations.

If your labs checklist has been approved by EHSO, forward it to your department head and await further instructions.
If you have not received approval from EHSO, please email labsafety@uic.edu.













            Screening, Monitoring, and Reporting
          Heading link



 
Copy link






                            Temperature and Wellness Reporting
                    








            Temperature and Wellness Reporting
          


Staff returning to the on-campus workplace must conduct symptom monitoring every day before reporting to work. Staff members must be free of ANY symptoms potentially related to COVID-19 or have had evaluation and clearance by University Health Services to be eligible to report to work.
Temperature monitoring will be required following established protocols. Access the UIC temperature reporting form here. For general information on temperature monitoring, refer to the COVID-19 Public Spaces and Office Safety Guidance document.

Guidance specific to the College of Engineering:
Each day an individual comes to campus, that person must fill out the UIC temperature and symptom reporting form. Based on the answers provided, the system will immediately return a result of “Admit” (in which case the person may come to campus) or “No Admit” (in which case the person may not come in).
When an individual scans a UIC ID card to enter a building, the system will note the entry and determine whether the person had received “Admit” clearance for the day. If an “Admit” clearance is not on file for that specific day, a violation will be entered in the card access system 30 minutes past the time of entry. Individuals who enter without submitting a reporting form will receive an email 30 minutes after entry asking them to submit the form and receive “Admit” clearance in order to remain on campus.
COE procedures for noncompliance are as follows:

For each notice of violation, the responsible lab safety manager will communicate with lab director (faculty PI), who will need to vouch in writing that the individual in violation is healthy and has subsequently submitted the reporting form.
Upon any violation, if a lab has had two prior violations during the past 30 days, the lab safety manager must notify the department head.
If any lab has had five violations during the past 30 days, the department must notify the dean.








